title: Bowman says triggering alarm ahead of House spending bill vote was 'innocent mistake'
description: U.S. Capitol Police are investigating after a fire alarm was triggered in a congressional office building on Saturday before the House vote on a stopgap spending bill.

title: The police chief who led a raid of a small Kansas newspaper has been suspended
description: The chief's suspension is a reversal for the town mayor.

title: WATCH:  Boy drives stolen construction vehicle, damages property
description: A 10-year-old boy was caught operating a stolen construction vehicle and driving it through a neighborhood, crushing a fence and damaging vehicles.

title: Federal agency sues Chipotle after a Kansas manager allegedly ripped off an employee's hijab
description: A manager at a Kansas location forcibly removed an employee's hijab.

title: WATCH:  Remote subs explore sunken WWII carriers
description: Undersea explorers used remote submersibles to capture the first footage of three WWII aircraft carriers sunk in the Pacific during the Battle of Midway.

title: U2 concert uses stunning visuals to open massive Sphere venue in Las Vegas
description: Two helicopters zoomed through the starlit skies before producing spotlights over a Las Vegas desert and U2 frontman Bono, who kneeled to ground while singing “Vertigo.”

title: Cleveland Browns tight end David Njoku burned on face, arm in home accident while lighting fire pit
description: Cleveland Browns tight end David Njoku listed as questionable for Sunday's game.

title: The Flying Scotsman locomotive collided with another train in Scotland. Several people were injured
description: Several people were injured after the Flying Scotsman steam locomotive crashed.

title: 6 miners killed, 15 trapped underground in collapse of gold mine: State media
description: Zimbabwe’s state broadcaster reports that the collapse of a gold mine has killed six people, while 15 more are trapped underground

title: Germany's government and Elon Musk spar on X over maritime rescue ships
description: Germany’s government has rebuked X owner Elon Musk after he criticized the recent work of migrant rescue ships that German humanitarian groups operate in the Mediterranean Sea

title: Deaf couple who made history scaling Everest aims to inspire others
description: Shayna Unger and Scott Lehmann became the first deaf Americans to climb to the top of Everest and they say they hope their story can inspire others in the community.

title: Putin marks anniversary of annexation of Ukrainian regions as drones attack overnight
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has released an address marking the one-year anniversary of Moscow’s unilateral annexation of four Ukrainian regions

title: Israeli soldiers kill a Palestinian man in West Bank, saying he threw explosives
description: Palestinian health officials say Israeli soldiers have shot and killed a Palestinian man in the West Bank

title: Illinois semitruck accident kills 1, injures 5 and prompts ammonia leak evacuation
description: Police say a semitruck carrying ammonia overturned in an Illinois county, spilling the chemical and causing an evacuation of area residents

title: Special counsel raises more concerns over Trump's attacks on witnesses
description: Special counsel raises more concerns over Trump's attacks on witnesses, suggests he may have violated law against purchasing firearm.

title: Former Staples exec sentenced in Varsity Blues scheme, marking end of years-long case
description: Former Staples executive John Wilson was sentenced on Friday to one year of probation for his role in the college admissions cheating scheme known as Varsity Blues.
